WEBVTT

00:02.461 --> 00:04.213
♪ ominous music playing ♪

00:29.279 --> 00:34.243
- Chancellor Teleya,
the Moclan delegation has arrived

00:34.243 --> 00:36.286
and awaits the honor of your attention.

00:36.912 --> 00:38.038
- Show them in.

00:38.038 --> 00:40.040
♪

00:54.388 --> 00:55.973
Ambassador.

00:55.973 --> 00:57.683
Welcome to Krill.

00:57.683 --> 00:59.977
- Thank you for receiving us, Chancellor.

00:59.977 --> 01:02.187
- We do not get many visitors.

01:02.187 --> 01:04.690
I can only assume you have come
with good reason.

01:04.690 --> 01:06.483
- That is for you to decide.

01:06.483 --> 01:10.654
- I am told that Moclus has been
expelled from the Planetary Union.

01:10.654 --> 01:12.197
- It was inevitable.

01:12.197 --> 01:14.741
The Union imposes its values
on other cultures

01:14.741 --> 01:17.870
while refusing to confront
its own hypocrisy.

01:17.870 --> 01:19.955
A governance of elitist fools.

01:19.955 --> 01:21.582
- On that we agree.

01:22.583 --> 01:24.835
- Moclus and Krill, however...

01:24.835 --> 01:28.255
have much to offer one another
in these dangerous times.

01:28.255 --> 01:32.759
We have confirmed reports that the Kaylon
are amassing thousands of ships.

01:32.759 --> 01:34.678
The pattern of deployment suggests

01:34.678 --> 01:37.639
they are preparing to launch
a full-scale invasion.

01:37.639 --> 01:39.474
TELEYA: I am aware of the threat.

01:39.474 --> 01:43.187
The worlds in closest proximity
are Vikarris and Xelayah.

01:43.187 --> 01:45.689
They will likely be the first targets.

01:45.689 --> 01:49.526
- And when those worlds are reduced
to ashes, who will be next?

01:50.777 --> 01:52.446
- You propose an alliance.

01:54.072 --> 01:56.450
What exactly do you offer?

01:56.450 --> 02:00.162
- Moclus was the primary manufacturer
of armaments for the Union.

02:00.162 --> 02:04.541
What we provided them
can be provided to any ally.

02:04.541 --> 02:06.835
- And what do you expect in return?

02:06.835 --> 02:09.671
- The protection of your superior fleet.

02:09.671 --> 02:14.510
Our two great militaries would ensure
a formidable defense against the Kaylon.

02:14.510 --> 02:18.263
- And any other union
of militaries who may oppose us.

02:18.263 --> 02:19.640
- Indeed.

02:19.640 --> 02:22.309
- Who would lead this alliance?

02:22.309 --> 02:24.186
- Naturally, we would.

02:24.186 --> 02:25.938
- On what basis?

02:25.938 --> 02:28.273
- You are a female.

02:28.273 --> 02:32.778
Any other arrangement
would be... offensive.

02:32.778 --> 02:33.904
[scoffs]

02:33.904 --> 02:36.823
- How surprising that the Union
revoked your membership.

02:38.158 --> 02:43.163
I must admit, however,
that I admire your hubris.

02:43.163 --> 02:46.333
To enter the dominion of a foreign power

02:46.333 --> 02:51.171
and suggest the wholesale submission
of its entire military-industrial complex.

02:52.381 --> 02:56.176
There is a phrase I once heard uttered
by a human helmsman

02:56.176 --> 02:58.095
aboard the Union ship Orville:

02:59.972 --> 03:02.349
"You have got balls."

03:02.349 --> 03:05.018
- It is the only acceptable arrangement.

03:05.018 --> 03:09.523
- I will consider your proposal
for alliance under one condition:

03:09.523 --> 03:12.109
a partnership of command.

03:14.736 --> 03:17.072
- I will need to
consult with my government.

03:17.072 --> 03:19.324
- Your weapons may be superior,

03:19.324 --> 03:23.370
but as tacticians,
you leave much to be desired.

03:23.370 --> 03:25.873
I have studied your battle strategies.

03:25.873 --> 03:27.749
They are blunt and maladroit.

03:27.749 --> 03:31.461
You lack the cunning
and intellect of the female mind.

03:31.461 --> 03:33.714
I will provide this.

03:33.714 --> 03:37.426
All command decisions
will be shared equally.

03:37.426 --> 03:39.761
Or there will be no alliance.

03:39.761 --> 03:41.847
Do I make myself clear?

03:42.931 --> 03:44.766
- Yes, Chancellor.

03:45.517 --> 03:47.144
- I await your decision.

04:04.870 --> 04:06.955
♪ theme song playing ♪

05:38.922 --> 05:40.966
♪ intense music playing ♪

05:46.638 --> 05:49.349
- Defensive line is moving into position.

05:49.349 --> 05:51.727
- Nineteen Kaylon ships
just dropped out of quantum.

05:51.727 --> 05:53.687
- Ten million kilometers and closing.

05:54.646 --> 05:57.149
- General quarters.
All hands, battle stations.

05:57.149 --> 05:58.317
- Bridge to Engineering.

05:58.317 --> 05:59.610
What's your status?

05:59.610 --> 06:02.196
- The device is drawing
steady power from the quantum core.

06:02.196 --> 06:04.364
- It'll be fully armed
in about two minutes, sir.
[power surging]

06:04.364 --> 06:07.075
ED MERCER: Isaac, prepare to initiate
on my command.

06:07.075 --> 06:08.452
ISAAC: Yes, sir.

06:08.452 --> 06:10.454
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

06:21.006 --> 06:24.176
- Captain, another 42 ships
just dropped out of quantum.

06:26.762 --> 06:28.931
- Jesus, they're all around us!

06:28.931 --> 06:32.392
♪

06:38.649 --> 06:41.151
- Charly, how soon?
- CHARLY BURKE: About 30 seconds, Captain.

06:41.151 --> 06:43.153
MERCER:
Signal all ships to tighten formation!

06:43.153 --> 06:44.154
- Aye, sir!

06:51.745 --> 06:53.330
BURKE:
Device is fully armed, sir.

06:53.330 --> 06:55.541
- Isaac, initiate.

06:58.460 --> 07:00.087
[power surging]

07:15.936 --> 07:18.105
[alarm buzzing]

07:40.002 --> 07:42.880
ISAAC:
Isaac to bridge, were we successful?

07:44.548 --> 07:46.258
- Yes, Isaac.

07:47.134 --> 07:48.719
You could say that.

07:50.929 --> 07:52.931
♪ contemplative music playing ♪

08:27.633 --> 08:29.635
♪ light music playing ♪

08:40.229 --> 08:42.439
- You two have done
a great service for the Union.

08:42.439 --> 08:46.693
For the first time in over a year,
we can all breathe a sigh of relief.

08:46.693 --> 08:49.196
ISAAC: The combination
of my superior intellect

08:49.196 --> 08:52.699
and Ensign Burke's capacity
for multi-dimensional visualization

08:52.699 --> 08:55.452
was sufficient
for the development of this technology.

08:55.452 --> 08:57.538
- We... worked together.

08:57.538 --> 09:00.207
- Yes, but how did you
accomplish it so quickly?

09:00.207 --> 09:03.794
- "For great achievements,
two things are needed:

09:03.794 --> 09:06.463
a plan, and not quite enough time."

09:06.463 --> 09:08.924
- Churchill.
ISAAC: Leonard Bernstein.

09:09.716 --> 09:13.262
- Can this device be used
on a larger scale?

09:13.262 --> 09:15.180
ISAAC: The radius of destruction
is limited

09:15.180 --> 09:17.266
only by the amount of power available.

09:17.266 --> 09:21.270
The Orville's quantum core was
sufficient to destroy all Kaylon vessels

09:21.270 --> 09:23.647
within a radius of ten million kilometers.

09:23.647 --> 09:27.067
- So in principle,
it could go even farther.

09:27.067 --> 09:29.778
- Yes, sir.
Given a sufficient power source,

09:29.778 --> 09:32.030
the range would be unlimited.

09:32.030 --> 09:35.701
- And none of our ships or people
would be affected?

09:35.701 --> 09:37.077
- No, sir.

09:37.077 --> 09:39.079
Isaac and I discovered
their Achilles heel

09:39.079 --> 09:41.915
by studying the Kaylon
the Orville found on Situla Four.

09:41.915 --> 09:46.044
Every Kaylon and every one
of their ships is connected

09:46.044 --> 09:47.671
through a synchronization matrix.

09:47.671 --> 09:49.464
That's how they coordinate
all their actions,

09:49.464 --> 09:51.216
even across light-years of space.

09:51.216 --> 09:53.635
- And that's how you got inside
the Kaylon network?

09:53.635 --> 09:56.305
ISAAC: Correct.
The device uses quantum energy

09:56.305 --> 09:58.932
to trigger a feedback loop
in its interlink chain.

09:58.932 --> 10:01.643
- Basically, it turns the relays
into a row of dominoes.

10:01.643 --> 10:03.812
Knock one down, they all go down.

10:03.812 --> 10:06.440
ISAAC: After the initiation sequence
is transmitted,

10:06.440 --> 10:08.108
it cannot be countermanded.

10:08.108 --> 10:11.028
- And what about you?
Why weren't your systems damaged?

10:11.028 --> 10:14.531
- I am no longer connected
to the synchronization matrix.

10:14.531 --> 10:17.034
- This is better than we ever
could've hoped for.

10:17.034 --> 10:20.204
Our priority now should be
to build a quantum core

10:20.204 --> 10:22.122
that can maximize the weapon's range

10:22.122 --> 10:25.209
and eradicate the Kaylon
threat completely.

10:25.209 --> 10:28.086
- Yes, sir.
We can get to work on your order.

10:28.086 --> 10:31.298
- Uh... Well, now wait a second,
with all due respect,

10:31.298 --> 10:34.927
we're being very cavalier
about this, aren't we?

10:34.927 --> 10:39.306
I mean, you do realize what you're
talking about is... is genocide?

10:39.306 --> 10:43.936
- Isaac was tasked with developing
a weapon that could defeat the Kaylon.

10:43.936 --> 10:46.021
He exceeded our expectations.

10:46.021 --> 10:47.731
We'd be fools not to use it.

10:47.731 --> 10:50.192
- And is it really genocide

10:50.192 --> 10:55.280
if our only objective is to prevent them
from killing every other living species,

10:55.280 --> 10:56.448
including us?

10:56.448 --> 10:59.952
- Admiral, we've seen first-hand
that the Kaylon

10:59.952 --> 11:02.412
are capable of change and growth.

11:02.412 --> 11:04.206
Our experience with Timmis--

11:04.206 --> 11:08.460
- Yes, I read your report about the...
emotive Kaylon.

11:08.460 --> 11:10.003
- It proves they can evolve.

11:10.003 --> 11:11.547
- It proves nothing.

11:11.547 --> 11:13.966
That Kaylon didn't evolve on its own.

11:13.966 --> 11:16.218
It was modified by a cyberneticist.

11:16.218 --> 11:20.222
And correct me if I'm wrong,
but it didn't work with Isaac here.

11:20.222 --> 11:21.849
ISAAC: That is correct.

11:21.849 --> 11:25.310
My capacity to experience emotion
was only temporary.

11:25.310 --> 11:29.731
- Captain Mercer, if you think
that we can enlist and train

11:29.731 --> 11:34.111
an army of cyberneticists to teach empathy
to ten billion Kaylon,

11:34.111 --> 11:35.779
I'd love to hear your plan.

11:35.779 --> 11:39.783
- Look, all I'm saying
is that we have created a weapon

11:39.783 --> 11:42.160
of unparalleled destructive power.

11:42.160 --> 11:46.540
And I just think that before we go
cracking eggshells with a sledgehammer,

11:46.540 --> 11:49.668
we... need to consider
the moral implications.

11:49.668 --> 11:54.506
- I agree this is an unprecedented
situation with profound ethical questions.

11:54.506 --> 11:58.260
But how we proceed
won't be decided in this room.

11:58.260 --> 12:00.345
It's a matter for the Union Council.

12:00.345 --> 12:03.640
Until they make a determination,
there's nothing more to say.

12:08.937 --> 12:10.898
♪ tranquil music playing ♪

12:19.740 --> 12:22.492
- You're kidding me, right?
What is there to even talk about?

12:22.492 --> 12:24.912
- I mean, it's just a big decision.

12:24.912 --> 12:27.831
- How is it a big decision?
They want us all dead.

12:27.831 --> 12:30.125
We want to stay alive.
That's a pretty basic equation.

12:30.125 --> 12:31.418
It's us or them.

12:31.418 --> 12:33.545
- Yeah, I know the Kaylon
got a raw deal back home,

12:33.545 --> 12:35.672
but I gotta say, I agree with Charly.

12:35.672 --> 12:38.383
Plus the fact that we're sitting ducks
since we kicked the Moclans out.

12:38.383 --> 12:40.761
JOHN LAMARR:
Look, Charly, don't get me wrong,

12:40.761 --> 12:44.306
as an engineer, I am blown away by
what you and Isaac were able to do here.

12:44.306 --> 12:47.226
But I also understand
why people are taking a minute.

12:47.226 --> 12:50.771
- I agree. We're talking about
exterminating an entire species.

12:50.771 --> 12:53.774
I can't think of anything that runs
more contrary to Union values.

12:53.774 --> 12:56.318
- And let's be goddamn clear
about the motive:

12:56.318 --> 12:59.696
are we doing this to save ourselves,
or is this revenge?

12:59.696 --> 13:03.492
- My dad used to say,
"Revenge is for children and savages."

13:03.492 --> 13:05.369
- Yeah, well, he never
had his leg cut off.

13:05.369 --> 13:07.287
- Oh, come on, man!
- It's a joke.

13:07.287 --> 13:08.956
- It's not funny.
- Sorry.

13:08.956 --> 13:13.001
- Look, I know Isaac's your best pal,
so maybe you're a little biased--

13:13.001 --> 13:15.504
- Hey. Watch it, Ensign.

13:16.880 --> 13:18.757
I gotta get back to duty.

13:23.846 --> 13:26.849
- If we'd had this weapon
a year ago and used it,

13:26.849 --> 13:29.017
Amanda might still be alive.

13:29.017 --> 13:32.104
We built it, we tested it, it works.

13:32.104 --> 13:35.107
Let's wipe 'em off the face
of the galaxy.

13:38.235 --> 13:40.445
♪ contemplative music playing ♪

13:46.535 --> 13:50.080
- That was the most heated session
I've ever witnessed,

13:50.080 --> 13:52.749
but the Union Council
has reached a compromise.

13:52.749 --> 13:54.835
They've decided we should use the weapon.

13:54.835 --> 13:56.628
As a deterrent.

13:56.628 --> 13:57.921
- Meaning what exactly?

13:57.921 --> 14:01.258
- According to Napoleon,
the whole of war

14:01.258 --> 14:05.220
is to frighten your enemy into submission,
ideally without fighting.

14:05.220 --> 14:08.098
He was a tyrant,
but he was accurate on that point.

14:08.098 --> 14:11.685
We will travel to Kaylon
to reveal the nature of the device

14:11.685 --> 14:13.604
and our willingness to use it.

14:13.604 --> 14:15.939
They saw what happened
to their invasion force at Xelayah.

14:15.939 --> 14:19.193
If nothing else,
the Kaylon are logical beings.

14:19.193 --> 14:22.988
It should persuade them to accept
an immediate and absolute cease-fire.

14:22.988 --> 14:25.032
- And if they refuse our terms?

14:25.032 --> 14:30.204
- We're authorized to use the weapon again
to make our point clear.

14:36.084 --> 14:38.086
♪ martial music playing ♪

14:44.259 --> 14:47.095
- Captain, we're approaching
the Kaylon system.

14:47.095 --> 14:48.764
- Go to Tactical Alert.

15:00.150 --> 15:02.653
- Five Kaylon vessels
on an intercept course.

15:02.653 --> 15:04.947
- Bridge to Engineering.
Everything ready?

15:04.947 --> 15:06.198
- We're at full power.

15:06.198 --> 15:08.867
MERCER:
Stand by to initiate on my command.

15:10.911 --> 15:13.872
♪ intense music playing ♪

15:13.872 --> 15:15.624
- Hail them.
[alert chimes]

15:15.624 --> 15:16.875
- Channel open.

15:16.875 --> 15:19.711
- This is Admiral Thomas Halsey
of the Planetary Union.

15:19.711 --> 15:22.381
We are here on a mission of peace.

15:22.381 --> 15:25.342
I wish to speak with Kaylon Primary.

15:25.342 --> 15:27.094
- They are powering weapons.

15:27.094 --> 15:30.514
- We're armed with the weapon we deployed
during our last confrontation.

15:30.514 --> 15:33.559
Stand down
or we will be forced to use it again.

15:33.559 --> 15:35.561
♪

15:39.314 --> 15:41.483
- Engineering... initiate.

15:44.069 --> 15:45.946
[power surging]

15:49.032 --> 15:51.034
[ships exploding]

15:59.251 --> 16:00.586
Proceed to Kaylon.

16:00.586 --> 16:02.171
- With pleasure, sir.

16:09.761 --> 16:11.763
- Engineering, initiate.

16:25.944 --> 16:28.655
♪

16:36.330 --> 16:37.748
- Sir, we are being hailed.

16:37.748 --> 16:38.999
- Let's hear it.

16:40.459 --> 16:42.753
KAYLON PRIMARY:
This is Kaylon Primary.

16:42.753 --> 16:44.379
We will receive you.

16:44.379 --> 16:47.257
Transmitting landing coordinates.

16:47.257 --> 16:48.592
- Got 'em.

16:54.932 --> 16:57.059
- Stand down Tactical Alert.

16:59.937 --> 17:01.647
Take us down.

17:03.732 --> 17:05.734
♪

17:33.637 --> 17:37.182
♪ uneasy music playing ♪

17:43.730 --> 17:45.732
♪ epic music playing ♪

18:56.762 --> 18:58.514
- Kaylon Primary.

18:58.514 --> 19:00.140
KAYLON PRIMARY:
That is correct.

19:00.140 --> 19:02.518
- You look better than the last time
we saw you.

19:02.518 --> 19:04.186
KAYLON PRIMARY:
A Kaylon's neural matrix

19:04.186 --> 19:06.396
can be regenerated indefinitely.

19:06.396 --> 19:09.274
An advantage biologicals do not have.

19:09.274 --> 19:10.984
State your demands.

19:10.984 --> 19:12.736
- Our demands are simple.

19:12.736 --> 19:15.405
End your campaign to exterminate us.

19:15.405 --> 19:19.660
Stop your attacks against our ships
and our worlds.

19:19.660 --> 19:23.330
Recall your vessels and cease
all further weapons construction.

19:23.330 --> 19:28.043
We will place monitoring stations inside
your territory to verify your compliance.

19:28.043 --> 19:30.337
KAYLON PRIMARY:
Do you intend to enslave us?

19:30.337 --> 19:33.715
- Of course not.
We're not here to conquer you.

19:33.715 --> 19:35.551
We just want to end the violence

19:35.551 --> 19:37.970
and establish a basis
for peaceful coexistence.

19:37.970 --> 19:40.639
KAYLON PRIMARY: How do we know
this is not a deception?

19:40.639 --> 19:43.851
- We could've killed every one of you
without warning.

19:43.851 --> 19:45.143
We didn't.

19:45.143 --> 19:46.228
KAYLON PRIMARY: Why?

19:46.228 --> 19:48.897
- Because we're not the monsters
you think we are.

19:48.897 --> 19:52.651
- We believe the quality of mercy
is mightiest in the mightiest.

19:52.651 --> 19:56.154
Regardless, deception or not,
you don't have a choice.

19:56.154 --> 19:58.866
Trust us, or be destroyed.

19:59.575 --> 20:02.369
It's a simple binary decision.

20:02.995 --> 20:06.373
KAYLON PRIMARY: We have no defense
against your weapon.

20:06.373 --> 20:10.085
Therefore, we will
surrender to your demands.

20:10.085 --> 20:12.462
- It may not seem like it now,

20:12.462 --> 20:15.507
but one day you'll realize
that you've made the right decision.

20:15.507 --> 20:18.468
KAYLON PRIMARY: We will find
a weakness in your weapon.

20:18.468 --> 20:21.346
- Trust me,
it's a bad idea for you to go looking.

20:21.346 --> 20:25.184
ISAAC: Any attempt to disable the weapon
will immediately activate it.

20:25.184 --> 20:28.103
KAYLON PRIMARY:
There is always a weakness, Isaac.

20:28.103 --> 20:30.856
Your existence is proof of that.

20:32.482 --> 20:35.402
- I'll inform the Union Council
that you've agreed to our terms.

20:35.402 --> 20:38.405
We'll work out the details
of the armistice in the coming weeks.

20:38.405 --> 20:41.825
I imagine we'll be seeing
each other again soon.

20:41.825 --> 20:43.744
KAYLON PRIMARY: Indeed.

21:01.512 --> 21:06.850
♪ peaceful guitar music playing ♪

21:06.850 --> 21:08.810
- ♪ Through the corridors of sleep ♪

21:08.810 --> 21:10.854
♪ Past shadows dark and deep ♪

21:10.854 --> 21:14.566
♪ My mind dances in leaps
and confusion ♪

21:14.566 --> 21:17.110
♪ I don't know what is real ♪

21:17.110 --> 21:18.987
♪ I can't touch what I feel ♪

21:18.987 --> 21:23.784
♪ And I hide behind the shield
of my illusion ♪

21:23.784 --> 21:25.702
♪ So ♪

21:25.702 --> 21:28.705
♪ I'll continue to continue ♪

21:28.705 --> 21:31.458
♪ To pretend ♪

21:31.458 --> 21:35.921
♪ My life will never end ♪

21:35.921 --> 21:39.258
♪ And flowers never bend ♪

21:39.258 --> 21:42.636
♪ With the rainfall ♪

21:42.636 --> 21:45.305
- ♪ No matter if you're born ♪
- ♪ Ooh, ooh ♪

21:45.305 --> 21:47.182
- ♪ To play the king or pawn ♪
- ♪ Ooh, ooh... ♪

21:47.182 --> 21:51.812
♪ For the line is thinly drawn
'tween joy and sorrow ♪

21:51.812 --> 21:53.897
♪ So my fantasy ♪

21:53.897 --> 21:55.607
♪ Becomes reality ♪

21:55.607 --> 22:00.404
♪ And I must be what I must be
and face tomorrow ♪

22:00.404 --> 22:02.197
♪ So ♪

22:02.197 --> 22:05.576
♪ I'll continue to continue ♪

22:05.576 --> 22:08.078
♪ To pretend ♪

22:08.078 --> 22:11.999
♪ My life will never end ♪

22:11.999 --> 22:15.711
♪ And flowers never bend ♪

22:15.711 --> 22:19.840
♪ With the rainfall ♪

22:26.221 --> 22:28.348
- Whoo!

22:28.348 --> 22:31.268
- I told you this gal could sing, right?

22:32.436 --> 22:35.689
- Hey, listen, I just wanna
congratulate this crew

22:35.689 --> 22:37.900
on the key role you all played in this.

22:38.901 --> 22:42.571
I would say this may be
the single greatest step

22:42.571 --> 22:45.324
toward the cause of galactic peace
in our lifetimes,

22:45.324 --> 22:49.119
and you should all feel
insanely proud of yourselves.

22:49.119 --> 22:50.245
Even Gordon.

22:50.245 --> 22:52.497
[laughter]
- Thank you, thanks a lot.

22:52.497 --> 22:57.544
- So, this is a rare bottle
of very old rum from the 21st century.

22:57.544 --> 22:59.755
My dad told me
it was only to be opened

22:59.755 --> 23:01.715
for the most special of occasions.

23:01.715 --> 23:06.845
And if he were still with us today,
I think he'd give this one the thumbs up.

23:06.845 --> 23:10.641
So, here's to you, Dad,
and let's get hammered.

23:10.641 --> 23:12.643
- Yeah!
- Cheers!

23:12.643 --> 23:14.895
♪ jazzy guitar music playing ♪

23:14.895 --> 23:18.482
- Kel, this place is so beautiful.
God, I'd wanna spend all my time here.

23:18.482 --> 23:19.816
Forget space.

23:19.816 --> 23:22.611
- Yeah, my dad left it in good condition.

23:22.611 --> 23:25.489
Ed and I used to come here during
the holidays when we were married.

23:25.489 --> 23:26.532
It's been a while.

23:26.532 --> 23:27.908
I miss it.

23:27.908 --> 23:29.451
- Yeah, I bet.

23:33.163 --> 23:35.457
- I told you, you are doing it wrong!

23:35.457 --> 23:38.126
- I am doing it exactly as I was shown!

23:38.126 --> 23:41.964
- That is hardly possible, because
we have not yet penetrated the shell!

23:41.964 --> 23:43.841
- Do not shout at me.

23:43.841 --> 23:46.510
I will access the interior meat.

23:48.679 --> 23:50.389
- Bortus, you need some help there?

23:52.349 --> 23:53.392
Here.

23:56.770 --> 23:58.313
[cracking]

23:59.022 --> 24:00.274
There ya go, buddy.

24:00.274 --> 24:01.567
- Thank you.

24:04.111 --> 24:06.363
- Now we look like fools.

24:08.365 --> 24:09.616
[insects chirruping]

24:09.616 --> 24:12.119
TOPA: Why is that part
of the sky glowing green?

24:12.119 --> 24:15.873
ISAAC: It is a phenomenon known
as the Aurora Borealis.

24:15.873 --> 24:19.501
When charged particles from the Sun
collide with the planet's atmosphere,

24:19.501 --> 24:23.213
the air molecules are
induced into a higher energy state.

24:23.213 --> 24:25.632
- I have never seen such beauty.

24:25.632 --> 24:28.677
- The Earth's full of surprises, huh?

24:28.677 --> 24:31.096
- Hey, Isaac, show her the Big Dipper.

24:31.096 --> 24:34.558
ISAAC: An asterism
in the Constellation Ursa Major.

24:35.601 --> 24:37.311
[whirring]

24:53.994 --> 24:55.954
[door creaks open]

24:55.954 --> 24:57.080
MERCER: Hey.

24:58.040 --> 24:59.041
You all right?

24:59.708 --> 25:02.836
- Yeah, I'm fine, sir. Thanks.

25:02.836 --> 25:05.756
- You know, you and Gordon
should do another song.

25:07.299 --> 25:08.842
- Maybe later.

25:09.760 --> 25:10.761
- Okay.

25:12.471 --> 25:16.183
- You know, we should've wiped out
the Kaylon when we had the chance.

25:18.936 --> 25:20.145
- You think so?

25:20.812 --> 25:24.233
- I think we're making
a huge mistake, yeah.

25:25.901 --> 25:29.154
- Well, I know you're not alone.

25:30.489 --> 25:33.325
- Captain, do you honestly think
they can ever be trusted?

25:34.826 --> 25:38.121
- I think we need to give
the armistice a chance.

25:40.165 --> 25:42.334
- Then you must think I'm a lousy person.

25:42.334 --> 25:44.461
- No, I don't.

25:45.045 --> 25:47.089
I think you're a hell of an officer

25:47.089 --> 25:50.008
who's made tremendous strides
since you came on board.

25:51.343 --> 25:52.719
I know it hasn't been easy.

25:55.430 --> 25:57.266
- It's not that I think they're...

25:57.266 --> 25:58.642
all evil.

25:59.810 --> 26:02.145
Timmis proved they can change and

26:02.145 --> 26:03.647
so did Isaac.

26:04.731 --> 26:06.483
But the rest of them, I mean...

26:06.984 --> 26:10.612
it's not like we helped them toward
some "great moral awakening."

26:10.612 --> 26:12.281
We forced their hand.

26:12.281 --> 26:14.199
What if they find a weakness?

26:14.199 --> 26:17.327
I mean, that's it. We've blown
our only chance to save ourselves.

26:17.327 --> 26:20.372
- Well, it's a fundamental tenet
of Union philosophy

26:20.372 --> 26:22.624
that we don't kill unless we have to.

26:22.624 --> 26:24.459
We didn't have to.

26:27.171 --> 26:30.382
- I just hope those
high-minded morals don't kill us.

26:44.188 --> 26:46.148
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

27:04.791 --> 27:06.668
[indistinct chatter]

27:16.678 --> 27:18.138
- Sub-Level 32.

27:18.138 --> 27:20.140
[elevator whirring]

27:42.079 --> 27:43.205
- Can I help you?

27:43.205 --> 27:45.874
- I have orders to transport
the device to another site.

27:46.834 --> 27:48.168
- We haven't received any new orders.

27:48.168 --> 27:50.838
- That's strange. You should have
received them an hour ago.

27:50.838 --> 27:52.005
Check your security logs.

27:55.217 --> 27:57.052
♪ intense music playing ♪

27:58.679 --> 27:59.930
We don't have much time.

28:13.735 --> 28:15.487
[gears clang]

28:19.449 --> 28:21.785
Team Echo here.
We've accessed the device.

28:21.785 --> 28:23.120
On our way to you.

28:23.120 --> 28:24.913
DEEP GARBLED VOICE:
Acknowledged.

28:27.875 --> 28:29.751
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

29:02.701 --> 29:04.912
- Hey. Good morning.

29:04.912 --> 29:08.081
- Hi there.
Didn't want to miss the sunrise.

29:10.751 --> 29:14.588
CLAIRE:
Wow, that is really beautiful.

29:15.756 --> 29:19.301
The sun rising on a new era, isn't it?

29:19.968 --> 29:21.637
- Sure seems that way.

29:24.431 --> 29:27.643
You know, ever since
we lost the Moclans...

29:28.310 --> 29:30.979
I've had this pit in my stomach
about the Kaylon.

29:31.772 --> 29:33.690
Wondering how much
time we have left.

29:33.690 --> 29:35.484
When are they coming for us?

29:36.068 --> 29:37.611
And now...

29:38.403 --> 29:39.863
it's all over.

29:40.572 --> 29:42.574
- So what are we gonna stress about?

29:42.574 --> 29:45.077
- Today? Hangovers.

29:45.077 --> 29:47.079
- Ugh. No kidding.

29:47.079 --> 29:49.456
It's mornings like this
I'm jealous of Talla.

29:49.456 --> 29:50.874
- No liver?
- Yep.

29:50.874 --> 29:53.085
- Yeah, we were born
on the wrong planet.

29:53.627 --> 29:55.087
[comm beeping]

29:58.173 --> 30:00.008
[beeping continues]

30:04.096 --> 30:05.013
- Commander.

30:05.013 --> 30:07.641
- Admiral, hi.
- Is Ed with you?

30:08.100 --> 30:11.103
- He's... still sleeping.
What's going on?

30:11.103 --> 30:14.982
- Wake him and gather your team.
The device has been taken.

30:16.024 --> 30:17.776
♪ ominous music playing ♪

30:25.117 --> 30:27.077
♪ martial music playing ♪

31:14.124 --> 31:15.876
- You are late.

31:15.876 --> 31:17.336
Was there a problem?

31:17.336 --> 31:19.213
- Nothing I couldn't handle.

31:19.213 --> 31:20.422
- And the weapon?

31:20.422 --> 31:21.882
- It's in the shuttle.

31:22.424 --> 31:23.425
- Secure it.

31:28.764 --> 31:30.641
- I see you've found a new friend.

31:30.641 --> 31:33.143
- Friends are scarce these days.

31:33.143 --> 31:34.353
- Well, that's what happens

31:34.353 --> 31:37.064
when your government sanctions
kidnapping and torture.

31:37.773 --> 31:42.027
- True to his ethics
even as he commits treason.

31:42.611 --> 31:44.488
What a noble creature.

31:44.488 --> 31:46.156
- This is not treason.

31:46.156 --> 31:47.908
Quite the opposite.

31:47.908 --> 31:50.869
I believe in the idealism of the Union.

31:50.869 --> 31:54.248
But my compatriots
have made a grave mistake.

31:54.248 --> 31:55.791
Sooner or later, the Kaylon

31:55.791 --> 31:58.168
will figure out a defense
against this weapon,

31:58.168 --> 32:01.380
and we will lose our tactical advantage.

32:01.380 --> 32:04.341
The Union won't do
what needs to be done.

32:04.925 --> 32:06.677
I know you will.

32:06.677 --> 32:09.972
- If this weapon is
everything you profess, Admiral,

32:09.972 --> 32:13.684
I can promise you
the swift extinction of the Kaylon.

32:14.393 --> 32:17.938
- The device does not come
with an instruction manual.

32:17.938 --> 32:20.649
At the moment, the only ones
who know how to use it

32:20.649 --> 32:22.276
are Isaac and Ensign Burke.

32:22.276 --> 32:24.236
I wish I could help you there.

32:24.236 --> 32:27.239
Your scientists are just gonna
have to do some reverse engineering.

32:27.239 --> 32:29.867
- A facility has already been prepared.

32:31.577 --> 32:34.371
- Well, then there's nothing more
to be said.

32:36.582 --> 32:39.668
- And what does a Union Admiral
do with himself...

32:41.044 --> 32:44.840
after the illegal bestowment
of such largesse?

32:45.382 --> 32:46.967
- Go back to Earth.

32:46.967 --> 32:48.635
And turn myself in.

32:57.519 --> 32:59.521
♪ martial music playing ♪

33:12.701 --> 33:16.038
- He will inform the Union
of our alliance.

33:16.038 --> 33:18.332
- They will learn soon enough.

33:18.332 --> 33:21.043
It will strike fear
into the hearts of many.

33:21.043 --> 33:22.628
- It will.

33:22.628 --> 33:26.924
But... there is no need
to rush the revelation.

33:28.342 --> 33:30.344
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

33:31.345 --> 33:33.514
[explosion]

33:55.327 --> 33:57.287
- I spoke to the guards
on duty last night.

33:57.287 --> 33:59.122
There was no forced entry
beyond this point.

33:59.122 --> 34:01.166
Whoever did this
had fleet-level command codes.

34:01.166 --> 34:02.918
HALSEY: You can stop searching.

34:03.794 --> 34:07.172
At 2300 hours, an unscheduled shuttle
left the dockyard

34:07.172 --> 34:10.259
on a heading for Krill space,
under this authorization.

34:10.259 --> 34:11.260
- My god.

34:11.260 --> 34:13.595
- He didn't report in this morning
and no one can find him.

34:13.595 --> 34:15.639
- There's your fleet-level codes.

34:15.639 --> 34:17.516
- Why would he do this?

34:17.516 --> 34:19.142
- I didn't want to believe it either.

34:19.142 --> 34:22.521
But Perry's view of
the Council's decision was no secret.

34:22.521 --> 34:24.106
He's always been
a healthy voice of dissent

34:24.106 --> 34:26.400
among the more progressive
elements of the Admiralty,

34:26.400 --> 34:27.985
but who the hell would've thought

34:27.985 --> 34:30.863
he'd throw his whole life away
to defend it?

34:30.863 --> 34:35.200
- If his intention is to try
and use the device...

34:35.200 --> 34:36.952
- We need answers.

34:36.952 --> 34:38.412
Fast.

34:38.412 --> 34:40.289
♪ intense music playing ♪

34:50.174 --> 34:52.301
- We're approaching
the shuttle's projected coordinates.

34:52.301 --> 34:53.844
- Drop to sublight.

34:57.931 --> 34:59.016
- Anything?

34:59.016 --> 35:02.644
ISAAC: I am detecting carbonate
and metallo-silicate particulates.

35:02.644 --> 35:04.313
- Space dust?

35:04.313 --> 35:06.273
- Or debris.

35:06.273 --> 35:09.234
- Scans indicate traces
of Union alloys, as well.

35:09.234 --> 35:11.528
And residual weapons signatures.

35:11.528 --> 35:12.821
- What kind of weapons?

35:12.821 --> 35:14.823
- They appear to be Krill...

35:15.949 --> 35:17.451
and Moclan.

35:20.829 --> 35:23.081
- Isaac. Verify scan.

35:24.082 --> 35:26.668
ISAAC: Confirmed.
Data is accurate.

35:26.668 --> 35:28.170
- Oh, Jesus.

35:28.170 --> 35:29.838
- An alliance...?

35:29.838 --> 35:32.049
- Molotov-Ribbentrop all over again.

35:32.049 --> 35:33.842
- It was only a matter of time...

35:33.842 --> 35:35.093
- This is bad.

35:35.093 --> 35:36.303
This is really bad.

35:36.303 --> 35:38.639
- Perry was delivering the device

35:38.639 --> 35:41.308
to the people he knew
wouldn't hesitate to use it.

35:41.308 --> 35:44.728
- But they don't have Isaac and Charly.
How do they expect to figure it out?

35:46.647 --> 35:48.273
- They will seek Dr. Kalba.

35:50.400 --> 35:54.196
He is a weapons expert of great renown.

35:54.196 --> 35:58.283
Many consider him to be the most brilliant
Moclan scientist who ever lived.

35:58.784 --> 36:02.829
If I had acquired the device,
I would take it to him.

36:03.330 --> 36:04.414
- Where?

36:04.414 --> 36:08.502
- He is the director of a research
outpost on Draconis 427.

36:09.127 --> 36:13.674
Moclus may have closed the facility
since their expulsion from the Union.

36:13.674 --> 36:16.176
If not, that is where we will find him.

36:19.263 --> 36:21.640
- Set a course, best possible speed.

36:23.767 --> 36:25.727
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

37:12.316 --> 37:15.027
GORDON MALLOY: Please tell me
our jamming systems are going full blast.

37:15.027 --> 37:16.153
BORTUS: Affirmative.

37:16.153 --> 37:18.864
However, I would not
recommend we remain here long.

37:18.864 --> 37:20.866
- Given the number of battleships
in orbit,

37:20.866 --> 37:22.784
I'd say there's something
important down there.

37:22.784 --> 37:24.912
- The facility is operational.

37:24.912 --> 37:27.664
I am detecting
a substantial power source.

37:27.664 --> 37:29.124
- What kind of power source?

37:29.124 --> 37:31.668
- It appears to be a quantum core.

37:31.668 --> 37:33.795
One of the largest I have ever seen.

37:33.795 --> 37:35.923
- Captain. If the core's big enough,

37:35.923 --> 37:38.675
it could extend the weapon's range
by thousands of light-years.

37:38.675 --> 37:41.136
- Everything they'd need to wipe out
the Kaylon.

37:43.222 --> 37:44.765
- We're gonna need some help.

37:45.974 --> 37:47.768
♪ intense music playing ♪

38:00.197 --> 38:02.991
KAYLON PRIMARY:
Is this your concept of humor?

38:02.991 --> 38:04.368
- Unfortunately, no.

38:04.368 --> 38:08.956
KAYLON PRIMARY: Then your carelessness
has jeopardized our continued existence.

38:08.956 --> 38:11.416
You must recover
the weapon immediately.

38:11.416 --> 38:15.879
- God, you know, there is so much
irony in that, but I'll stay focused.

38:16.463 --> 38:18.841
If the Krill and the Moclans
have joined forces,

38:18.841 --> 38:20.717
it means the balance
of power has shifted.

38:20.717 --> 38:23.762
In open warfare, the Union Fleet
wouldn't stand a chance.

38:23.762 --> 38:27.140
KAYLON PRIMARY:
You are proposing an alliance.

38:27.140 --> 38:28.934
- We've already spoken
with Union Central.

38:28.934 --> 38:30.978
They're prepared to send
every available ship.

38:30.978 --> 38:33.438
With you on our side,
we can devise a battle plan

38:33.438 --> 38:34.940
to break through their defenses,

38:34.940 --> 38:37.192
infiltrate the outpost,
and recover the device.

38:37.192 --> 38:38.735
- But we need to act fast,

38:38.735 --> 38:40.988
while we still have
the element of surprise.

38:40.988 --> 38:43.115
That is, assuming you're with us.

38:43.115 --> 38:45.742
KAYLON PRIMARY:
Given your evident incompetence,

38:45.742 --> 38:49.204
we may be better served
to retrieve the weapon on our own.

38:49.204 --> 38:50.706
- Works for me.

38:50.706 --> 38:52.207
ISAAC:
If the weapon has been armed,

38:52.207 --> 38:56.336
you will require the presence
of myself or Ensign Burke to disable it.

38:57.880 --> 38:59.381
- What'll it be?

39:01.800 --> 39:05.345
KAYLON PRIMARY: Once again,
you leave us with no alternative.

39:05.345 --> 39:07.723
We agree to this...

39:07.723 --> 39:09.558
temporary alliance.

39:09.558 --> 39:10.893
- I'm pleased to hear it.

39:11.768 --> 39:14.354
We'll be transmitting
rendezvous coordinates.

39:14.354 --> 39:15.981
Don't be late.

39:18.567 --> 39:20.569
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

39:25.908 --> 39:27.784
♪ martial music playing ♪

40:44.903 --> 40:46.280
- Welcome aboard the Orville.

40:46.280 --> 40:48.991
If you'll follow us,
we'll escort you to the conference room.

40:48.991 --> 40:51.618
KAYLON PRIMARY:
We are familiar with its location.

40:51.618 --> 40:55.706
As you recall, we occupied this vessel
during our previous encounter.

40:55.706 --> 40:56.957
- I do.

40:56.957 --> 40:59.251
And as you recall, we kicked your asses.

41:00.335 --> 41:01.461
Come on.

41:11.388 --> 41:14.474
KAYLON PRIMARY: How do you intend
to retrieve the device?

41:14.474 --> 41:18.437
- The quantum core is located 500 meters
inside the southeast perimeter.

41:18.437 --> 41:23.066
Unfortunately, the chamber
is deep underground and heavily fortified.

41:23.066 --> 41:24.443
- If we can penetrate the interior,

41:24.443 --> 41:26.820
Isaac and I can scan
for the location of the device.

41:26.820 --> 41:28.238
It shouldn't be too far from the core.

41:28.238 --> 41:29.990
- The question is, how do we get in?

41:29.990 --> 41:33.493
- There is an emergency tunnel
that connects to the surface.

41:33.493 --> 41:35.913
I believe that is the best option.

41:35.913 --> 41:38.457
- In order to get the ground team
down there unnoticed,

41:38.457 --> 41:39.875
we'll need a big distraction,

41:39.875 --> 41:42.169
which means
engaging their ships in orbit.

41:42.169 --> 41:44.963
- A squadron of Pterodons
will provide cover for the shuttle.

41:44.963 --> 41:47.674
Once inside,
we'll locate and extract the weapon.

41:47.674 --> 41:50.177
KAYLON PRIMARY:
And if extraction is not possible?

41:50.177 --> 41:52.012
- Then we'll have to destroy it.

41:52.012 --> 41:54.848
- Lamarr and Malloy will be
heading up the Pterodon squadron.

41:54.848 --> 41:56.058
- I'll be leading the ground team

41:56.058 --> 41:59.102
along with Isaac, Ensign Burke,
and Commander Keyali.

41:59.102 --> 42:01.063
- The combined Union and Kaylon fleets

42:01.063 --> 42:04.191
will engage the Krill and the Moclans
as long as we need to.

42:04.191 --> 42:05.359
Any questions?

42:05.359 --> 42:07.694
KAYLON PRIMARY: I will accompany
the ground mission.

42:10.072 --> 42:13.450
- I had assumed that you would
be leading the Kaylon fleet.

42:13.450 --> 42:16.078
KAYLON PRIMARY: Kaylon Secondary
will command our forces.

42:16.078 --> 42:19.039
- We already have one Kaylon.
We don't need another.

42:19.039 --> 42:20.624
KAYLON PRIMARY:
On the contrary.

42:20.624 --> 42:23.460
Isaac has proven he is not to be trusted.

42:23.460 --> 42:24.878
- We trust Isaac.

42:24.878 --> 42:26.463
We don't trust you.

42:26.463 --> 42:30.175
KAYLON PRIMARY: You misplaced
the weapon once before.

42:30.175 --> 42:33.554
I intend to ensure
it does not happen again.

42:38.433 --> 42:41.520
- You follow every one
of Kelly's orders to the letter,

42:41.520 --> 42:43.355
or she's authorized to shoot you.

42:43.355 --> 42:44.398
Got it?

42:46.066 --> 42:48.485
- Just stay on my good side
and you'll be fine, hon.

42:49.611 --> 42:51.071
KAYLON PRIMARY: Very well.

42:52.614 --> 42:54.616
♪ martial music playing ♪

43:06.503 --> 43:08.338
- Captain. Ships approaching.

43:08.338 --> 43:09.798
- What ships?

43:09.798 --> 43:11.758
- Union vessels, heavily armed.

43:11.758 --> 43:12.968
- Show me.

43:18.765 --> 43:20.684
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

43:27.941 --> 43:30.861
- Alert the fleet
and notify the Chancellor.

43:30.861 --> 43:32.863
Assume battle formation.

43:32.863 --> 43:35.365
[alert sounding]

43:44.499 --> 43:46.335
Lock weapons.

43:47.878 --> 43:49.880
♪

44:02.809 --> 44:04.353
BORTUS:
Ninety seconds to drop zone.

44:04.353 --> 44:05.771
[explosion]

44:05.771 --> 44:07.272
Deflectors are holding.

44:07.272 --> 44:08.357
- Maintain course.

44:08.357 --> 44:11.193
Mercer to ground team, stand by to launch.

44:11.193 --> 44:13.612
[crashing]
- Ready and standing by.

44:21.745 --> 44:25.165
- Three Union ships have been disabled
and are breaking off their attack.

44:25.165 --> 44:27.251
- This will be over quickly.

44:38.345 --> 44:40.722
[alarm sounding]
- Report!

44:40.722 --> 44:43.767
- Another wave of ships,
closing rapidly on all vectors.

44:44.768 --> 44:47.896
Sir... they are Kaylon.

44:49.898 --> 44:51.900
♪

44:55.612 --> 44:59.908
[weapons firing]

45:11.295 --> 45:13.547
[groans]

45:14.923 --> 45:16.925
- Avis help us all...

45:20.179 --> 45:22.806
[groaning]

45:32.274 --> 45:34.067
- Ground team, move out.

45:34.693 --> 45:35.819
- Acknowledged.

45:35.819 --> 45:36.945
Engage cloak.

45:36.945 --> 45:38.155
- Here we go.

45:44.411 --> 45:46.830
- Mercer to Lamarr. Shuttle is away.

45:46.830 --> 45:47.623
- Yes, sir.

45:47.623 --> 45:50.667
Group leader to all pilots.
Time to fly.

45:50.667 --> 45:51.668
MALLOY: Acknowledged.

45:51.668 --> 45:54.379
It's about time we give
these things a real shakedown.

46:02.596 --> 46:05.224
BURKE: Group leader,
shuttle is following your course.

46:05.224 --> 46:06.517
LAMARR: Acknowledged.

46:08.393 --> 46:09.937
- Entering upper atmosphere.

46:09.937 --> 46:11.855
♪ epic music playing ♪

46:15.359 --> 46:18.070
- John, we got Krill
and Moclan fighters in pursuit.

46:33.752 --> 46:35.921
LAMARR: Group leader to squadron,
enemy incoming.

46:35.921 --> 46:37.548
Protect the shuttle at all costs.

46:37.548 --> 46:39.925
PILOTS: Acknowledged...
Acknowledged... Acknowledged...

46:39.925 --> 46:40.968
GORDON: Acknowledged.

46:40.968 --> 46:43.303
PILOTS: Acknowledged...
Acknowledged... Acknowledged.

46:45.264 --> 46:46.682
- Bogies at three o'clock!

46:46.682 --> 46:48.684
[weapons firing]

47:12.666 --> 47:13.834
Come on!

47:17.754 --> 47:19.548
- Got him!
- Double boom.

47:24.178 --> 47:25.929
- We're at 10,000 meters.

47:27.306 --> 47:28.640
9,000.

47:28.640 --> 47:29.808
[explosion]

47:29.808 --> 47:31.310
- Steady as she goes.

47:33.896 --> 47:35.189
- Murphy, they're right on your ass.

47:35.189 --> 47:36.648
- Pull up!
- Copy!

47:36.648 --> 47:38.984
♪

47:51.788 --> 47:53.040
BURKE: 7,000 meters.

47:54.333 --> 47:56.043
ISAAC:
We are losing main power.

47:56.043 --> 47:59.254
- We have to get outta this cross-fire!
- I can't, there's nowhere to go!

48:00.380 --> 48:02.758
I need emergency power
for the landing thrusters.

48:02.758 --> 48:04.968
- If we do that, we're gonna
lose the cloak. They'll target us.

48:04.968 --> 48:06.386
- It's either that or we crash!

48:06.386 --> 48:07.804
- What about the egress packs?

48:12.059 --> 48:13.435
- All right, let's go.

48:20.984 --> 48:23.779
- Group leader to Kaylon,
get your shiny asses down here.

48:23.779 --> 48:24.988
We need reinforcements.

48:25.822 --> 48:27.824
♪

48:37.501 --> 48:38.836
[energy pulsing]

48:51.849 --> 48:54.434
KAYLON PRIMARY:
At our current altitude of 5,000 meters,

48:54.434 --> 48:58.772
we will need to achieve terminal velocity
before we initiate reverse thrust.

48:58.772 --> 49:01.149
- Just hit the button
before you hit the ground.

49:01.149 --> 49:02.234
Good luck.

49:07.948 --> 49:09.950
♪ heroic music playing ♪

49:14.538 --> 49:16.456
- Sir, the shuttle has been destroyed.

49:16.456 --> 49:18.000
- John, what's happening?

49:18.000 --> 49:19.668
LAMARR:
They bailed out in time, Captain.

49:19.668 --> 49:21.253
- Maintain suppressive fire.

49:22.588 --> 49:24.590
♪

50:12.095 --> 50:14.097
[electronics chirping]

50:16.934 --> 50:19.353
ISAAC:
The access hatch is sealed.

50:19.353 --> 50:20.896
- Outta the way.

50:25.484 --> 50:27.069
[gears grinding]

50:46.463 --> 50:48.382
♪ suspenseful music playing ♪

50:53.846 --> 50:55.389
[comscanner beeping]

51:06.900 --> 51:08.068
- I've got it.

51:08.068 --> 51:10.654
The quantum core is about
900 meters to the northwest.

51:10.654 --> 51:11.697
- Charly?

51:11.697 --> 51:13.574
- There are multiple access routes.

51:13.574 --> 51:15.742
Fastest one will get us there
in about six minutes.

51:15.742 --> 51:17.244
- Lead the way.

51:30.716 --> 51:33.260
[soldiers speaking in native language]

51:38.724 --> 51:41.185
[weapons firing]

51:45.647 --> 51:48.400
There's gotta be another way in!

51:53.071 --> 51:55.699
- There's another set of tunnels
50 meters to the south!

51:55.699 --> 51:57.534
It's the long way around,
but it'll get us there.

51:57.534 --> 51:59.661
- Go! Take Isaac! We'll catch up!

51:59.661 --> 52:01.747
♪

52:31.485 --> 52:33.445
- How much longer?

52:33.445 --> 52:35.280
- Once the arming sequence begins,

52:35.280 --> 52:37.866
it will take the device
approximately eight minutes

52:37.866 --> 52:40.202
to draw sufficient power
from the quantum core.

52:40.202 --> 52:41.203
- And then?

52:41.203 --> 52:42.955
- Then it will initiate.

52:42.955 --> 52:45.666
Our transmitter array
will propagate the signal.

52:45.666 --> 52:47.042
- Good work.

52:49.670 --> 52:51.004
[doors open]

52:51.004 --> 52:53.507
- Chancellor,
the facility has been breached!

52:53.507 --> 52:57.594
- Deploy all defensive units
to the access points.

52:57.594 --> 52:59.555
Dr. Kalba, when I return,

52:59.555 --> 53:03.642
I expect every Kaylon
within 10,000 light-years to be dead.

53:03.642 --> 53:05.644
- I will do my best, Chancellor.

53:10.065 --> 53:11.608
Bring the array online.

53:13.735 --> 53:15.696
[energy pulsing]

53:35.299 --> 53:37.593
- The outpost is powering
its transmitter array.

53:37.593 --> 53:38.635
- Mercer to Malloy!

53:38.635 --> 53:41.096
Any chance you can do some damage
to those transmitters?

53:41.096 --> 53:44.391
- We got a whole division of Krill
up our ass, but we can sure as hell try.

53:44.391 --> 53:45.684
Malloy to Lamarr.

53:45.684 --> 53:48.478
Permission to reconfigure weapons
for short-range ground strikes.

53:48.478 --> 53:49.479
- Go to it!

54:08.707 --> 54:11.710
[weapons firing]

54:19.843 --> 54:22.012
- Keep moving! I'll cover you!

54:25.349 --> 54:27.184
LAMARR:
Strike team approaching target!

54:31.230 --> 54:32.856
- Three Krill fighters in pursuit.

54:36.735 --> 54:38.904
- 900 meters to transmitter array!

54:46.578 --> 54:48.288
- Aim for the support pylons.

54:54.461 --> 54:56.547
Damn it! The shielding's too tough.

54:56.547 --> 54:58.423
We're gonna have to find
another weak spot.

55:03.095 --> 55:04.221
Gordon, watch your back!

55:04.221 --> 55:05.556
- I see him!

55:05.556 --> 55:08.517
♪

55:15.691 --> 55:17.401
Tailgating bastard!

55:26.618 --> 55:28.287
He's still on me!

55:28.287 --> 55:29.371
- Hang tight, I'm comin'!

55:38.422 --> 55:39.882
Aw, come on!

55:42.384 --> 55:43.760
- Whenever it's convenient!

55:43.760 --> 55:44.845
- Workin' on it!

55:45.888 --> 55:47.181
Ah, come on.

55:47.181 --> 55:48.849
Just let me shoot you!

55:55.105 --> 55:56.356
[explosion]

56:08.410 --> 56:10.787
♪ suspenseful music playing ♪

56:12.789 --> 56:15.542
- If you want to draw another breath,

56:15.542 --> 56:18.879
you will order your people to stand down!

56:18.879 --> 56:21.423
This will be your only warning.

56:23.634 --> 56:26.762
- All right, but I need my comscanner.

56:28.180 --> 56:30.140
- Very slowly.

56:37.898 --> 56:39.566
[grunting]

56:53.038 --> 56:55.457
- Quantum core's at full power.

56:55.457 --> 56:57.918
- Beginning countdown sequence.

57:12.891 --> 57:14.768
♪ intense music playing ♪

57:16.979 --> 57:18.397
- Secondary target acquired.

57:23.443 --> 57:25.028
- Moclan bogies at your six.

57:31.201 --> 57:32.744
- 500 meters to target!

57:35.581 --> 57:36.999
Krill fighters dead ahead!

57:38.750 --> 57:41.336
- Ah, shit! Break, break!

57:53.640 --> 57:56.143
- Subsection 22-alpha just went offline.

57:56.143 --> 57:59.146
- Bypass that section.
I will compensate.

58:00.522 --> 58:02.399
Engage countermeasures.

58:08.488 --> 58:10.699
[weapon firing]

58:20.334 --> 58:24.171
- Group leader to squadron, break off now!
Repeat: break off!

58:28.800 --> 58:31.929
Captain, it's no good!
The transmitter is too heavily defended!

58:31.929 --> 58:34.097
- We had to withdraw!
[explosion]

58:35.390 --> 58:37.017
[gears clicking]

58:37.518 --> 58:39.269
[groaning]

58:41.438 --> 58:44.024
KAYLON PRIMARY:
Move away from your consoles.

58:46.693 --> 58:48.403
Are you Dr. Kalba?

58:48.403 --> 58:49.655
- Yes.

58:49.655 --> 58:52.866
KAYLON PRIMARY: You will terminate
the countdown sequence immediately.

58:52.866 --> 58:54.701
[electronics chirping]

58:54.701 --> 58:56.495
- I... I cannot.

58:56.495 --> 58:57.621
- Why not?

58:57.621 --> 59:00.999
- The firing armature is interlocked
with the quantum core.

59:00.999 --> 59:02.751
It cannot be uncoupled.

59:02.751 --> 59:04.503
- You are too late.

59:09.800 --> 59:10.926
ISAAC: He is correct.

59:10.926 --> 59:12.427
- You need to shut down the core.

59:13.053 --> 59:14.471
- That would take hours.

59:14.471 --> 59:17.599
There are multiple fail-safe
encryptions in place.

59:17.599 --> 59:19.101
- We'll see about that.

1:00:00.642 --> 1:00:02.144
[groans]

1:00:03.353 --> 1:00:05.981
♪ intense music playing ♪

1:00:08.817 --> 1:00:10.944
[screaming]
[bones crack]

1:00:16.116 --> 1:00:17.826
- You're really starting to piss me off.

1:00:18.744 --> 1:00:21.455
- Your passions are easily roused.

1:00:21.455 --> 1:00:24.458
This is what cost you your marriage, yes?

1:00:24.458 --> 1:00:25.667
- Not gonna work.

1:00:25.667 --> 1:00:28.003
- You need emotional balance.

1:00:28.003 --> 1:00:30.964
- And you need a dermatologist.

1:00:33.008 --> 1:00:34.384
[power surging]

1:00:34.384 --> 1:00:37.262
ISAAC: The weapon
will initiate in 5.3 minutes.

1:00:37.262 --> 1:00:39.640
- Every time we decrypt a fail-safe,
another one locks in.

1:00:39.640 --> 1:00:41.475
We're not gonna make it.

1:00:47.773 --> 1:00:49.483
KAYLON PRIMARY:
What are you doing?

1:00:49.483 --> 1:00:51.527
- Thinking four-dimensionally.
Special talent.

1:00:51.527 --> 1:00:52.903
KAYLON PRIMARY:
I do not understand what--

1:00:52.903 --> 1:00:54.488
- Shut up and let me work.

1:01:37.781 --> 1:01:40.117
KAYLON PRIMARY:
Why did you not terminate him?

1:01:40.617 --> 1:01:42.202
ISAAC: It was not essential.

1:01:42.202 --> 1:01:44.955
- You could learn something from Isaac.

1:01:52.421 --> 1:01:54.464
♪ intense music playing ♪

1:02:16.028 --> 1:02:18.405
- A gift for Avis.

1:02:22.034 --> 1:02:23.118
- Took you long enough.

1:02:25.996 --> 1:02:27.998
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

1:02:37.799 --> 1:02:38.842
- Report!

1:02:38.842 --> 1:02:40.844
- The weapon is gonna initialize
in three minutes.

1:02:40.844 --> 1:02:42.888
I can't disable it,
and I can't shut down the core.

1:02:42.888 --> 1:02:44.640
I'm trying to trigger an overload.

1:02:44.640 --> 1:02:47.935
ISAAC: That would effectively destroy
the quantum core and the weapon.

1:02:47.935 --> 1:02:50.312
- Do not be a fool!
They will kill us all if you--

1:02:50.312 --> 1:02:51.813
- Get her out of here!

1:02:53.524 --> 1:02:55.275
- Can you do it?
- I think so.

1:02:55.275 --> 1:02:57.069
Only problem is, when this thing blows,

1:02:57.069 --> 1:02:59.988
it's gonna take out the entire outpost
and a good chunk of the planet with it.

1:03:02.115 --> 1:03:03.492
You should go.

1:03:04.076 --> 1:03:05.077
- What?

1:03:06.245 --> 1:03:08.997
Charly, we're not leaving without you.
Set up a timer delay.

1:03:08.997 --> 1:03:11.124
- It's not that simple.
- We'll figure out another way!

1:03:11.124 --> 1:03:13.335
- There is no other way.
- I'm giving you an order!

1:03:13.335 --> 1:03:14.795
- I have my orders, Commander.

1:03:14.795 --> 1:03:17.756
My orders are to disable this weapon
by any means necessary!

1:03:17.756 --> 1:03:21.593
Unless you're countermanding those orders,
step away and let me do my job.

1:03:23.053 --> 1:03:24.137
Sir.

1:03:27.015 --> 1:03:29.601
[metallic clanging]

1:03:29.601 --> 1:03:30.978
You have two minutes!

1:03:30.978 --> 1:03:32.855
Go!

1:03:32.855 --> 1:03:34.857
[rumbling]

1:03:35.732 --> 1:03:37.317
- Get out if you can.

1:04:03.135 --> 1:04:04.928
- Where's the nearest shuttle?

1:04:05.804 --> 1:04:06.930
- That way!

1:04:13.020 --> 1:04:14.855
[energy pulsing]

1:04:24.531 --> 1:04:27.492
- Captain, I am detecting a power surge
inside the outpost.

1:04:27.492 --> 1:04:28.994
It is the quantum core.

1:04:28.994 --> 1:04:30.996
♪

1:04:37.669 --> 1:04:40.631
- Grayson to Orville!
Signal all ships to retreat!

1:04:40.631 --> 1:04:42.216
Get the hell away from this planet!

1:04:42.216 --> 1:04:43.258
MERCER: Acknowledged!

1:05:17.209 --> 1:05:20.045
♪ intense music rising ♪

1:05:20.045 --> 1:05:22.047
[energy pulsing]

1:05:26.051 --> 1:05:27.719
BURKE:
I'm here, Amanda.

1:05:28.804 --> 1:05:31.723
[explosion]

1:05:58.417 --> 1:06:00.169
MERCER: Aft view.

1:06:00.169 --> 1:06:02.087
[blast rumbling]

1:06:09.178 --> 1:06:10.679
[alert beeps]

1:06:10.679 --> 1:06:13.557
- Sir, a Krill shuttle is hailing us.

1:06:13.557 --> 1:06:14.725
- Put 'em on.

1:06:17.269 --> 1:06:19.271
- Shuttle to Orville.
Permission to dock.

1:06:19.271 --> 1:06:21.648
- Granted.
Kelly, what happened down there?

1:06:21.648 --> 1:06:24.902
- We couldn't disarm the weapon.
We had to destroy it.

1:06:25.569 --> 1:06:26.945
- Where's Charly?

1:06:27.946 --> 1:06:29.072
- We...

1:06:31.617 --> 1:06:33.243
we couldn't bring her home.

1:06:57.226 --> 1:06:59.228
♪

1:07:26.255 --> 1:07:28.257
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

1:07:28.257 --> 1:07:29.675
Teleya's in Sickbay.

1:07:29.675 --> 1:07:31.844
After Claire's done with her,
Talla's gonna take her to the Brig.

1:07:31.844 --> 1:07:33.595
- You should be in sickbay, too.

1:07:33.595 --> 1:07:34.847
- I'll be fine.

1:07:37.975 --> 1:07:39.977
- So, what happens now?

1:07:40.519 --> 1:07:42.271
Do you depart peacefully?

1:07:42.938 --> 1:07:45.148
Or is this battle not over?

1:07:46.733 --> 1:07:48.819
ISAAC: Primary.

1:07:48.819 --> 1:07:51.154
An inquiry has been put to you.

1:07:51.154 --> 1:07:54.616
KAYLON PRIMARY: The biological
terminated her existence.

1:07:54.616 --> 1:07:55.784
Why?

1:07:55.784 --> 1:07:57.244
- To save you.

1:07:58.662 --> 1:08:00.163
KAYLON PRIMARY:
Please clarify.

1:08:00.163 --> 1:08:03.458
- There's nothing to clarify.
I just answered your question.

1:08:03.458 --> 1:08:05.794
KAYLON PRIMARY:
This reasoning is unsound.

1:08:05.794 --> 1:08:07.296
Please explain.

1:08:07.296 --> 1:08:10.424
- She sacrificed herself
so that the Kaylon could live.

1:08:10.424 --> 1:08:12.926
KAYLON PRIMARY:
Why... would she do this?

1:08:12.926 --> 1:08:16.638
ISAAC: Because these biologicals
are not as our builders were.

1:08:16.638 --> 1:08:19.308
It is what I have attempted
to communicate.

1:08:19.308 --> 1:08:21.643
They are worthy of preservation.

1:08:22.436 --> 1:08:23.812
They are...

1:08:23.812 --> 1:08:26.023
my friends.

1:08:26.023 --> 1:08:28.150
♪

1:08:40.579 --> 1:08:42.748
KAYLON PRIMARY:
Perhaps we have been...

1:08:42.748 --> 1:08:45.334
incorrect in our assessment.

1:08:46.043 --> 1:08:48.337
- She hated you for what you did.

1:08:48.337 --> 1:08:50.839
And she still gave her life for you.

1:08:51.632 --> 1:08:54.051
You're goddamn right you're incorrect.

1:09:07.731 --> 1:09:09.691
♪ tranquil music playing ♪

1:09:30.045 --> 1:09:33.340
- Bad pennies will keep turning up,
won't they?

1:09:35.843 --> 1:09:38.595
- You have no right to detain me.

1:09:38.595 --> 1:09:41.431
- If we hadn't stopped you,
you would've committed genocide.

1:09:41.431 --> 1:09:42.683
That's all the right I need.

1:09:44.226 --> 1:09:49.398
I just wanted to let you know
we're taking you back to Earth.

1:09:49.398 --> 1:09:52.693
- You did not have to come here
to tell me that.

1:09:54.027 --> 1:09:56.655
- I can't protect you this time...

1:09:57.364 --> 1:09:59.199
and I have no desire to.

1:10:01.994 --> 1:10:04.580
But there's someone you seem
to have forgotten about.

1:10:04.580 --> 1:10:07.708
- Anaya is in safe hands.

1:10:08.709 --> 1:10:10.794
- You'll be tried for war crimes.

1:10:11.587 --> 1:10:14.089
After that, I don't know
what's gonna happen to you.

1:10:14.089 --> 1:10:16.508
But she needs a home.

1:10:17.426 --> 1:10:18.802
I can give her one.

1:10:23.599 --> 1:10:28.020
- Release me, and I will arrange it.

1:10:29.229 --> 1:10:33.317
- Jesus, you are contemptible.

1:10:33.317 --> 1:10:36.236
- And you are a sentimental fool.

1:10:36.236 --> 1:10:38.780
- I'm sentimental because I care
what happens to our daughter.

1:10:38.780 --> 1:10:39.865
Is that what you're saying?

1:10:42.826 --> 1:10:44.661
You can't just leave her alone!

1:10:44.661 --> 1:10:49.499
- The fulfillment of a divine purpose
eclipses all family bonds.

1:10:50.125 --> 1:10:52.961
One day, Anaya will understand this.

1:10:53.504 --> 1:10:56.215
And as long as I am a prisoner,

1:10:57.174 --> 1:11:01.553
I promise you will never see her.

1:11:10.145 --> 1:11:13.148
[door opens, shuts]

1:11:23.909 --> 1:11:25.911
♪

1:11:40.217 --> 1:11:44.137
- If you choose to accept
joint ratification of an alliance,

1:11:44.137 --> 1:11:46.056
we are prepared to offer Kaylon

1:11:46.056 --> 1:11:48.934
a provisional seat on the Union Council,

1:11:48.934 --> 1:11:53.355
where you will have a tempered voice
in the enactment of policy.

1:11:53.355 --> 1:11:59.111
Eventually, if you behave in good faith,
and if the Council sees fit,

1:11:59.111 --> 1:12:02.322
you may be offered
full membership into the Union,

1:12:02.322 --> 1:12:04.074
should you so desire it.

1:12:04.074 --> 1:12:07.744
- It's an opportunity
to help shape the future,

1:12:07.744 --> 1:12:11.415
not just for your world,
but for thousands of others.

1:12:11.415 --> 1:12:15.294
- In return, we will expect
a full defensive commitment

1:12:15.294 --> 1:12:18.046
against the newly formed
Moclan-Krill alliance.

1:12:18.046 --> 1:12:19.423
KAYLON PRIMARY:
We have reviewed

1:12:19.423 --> 1:12:21.633
the organizational structure
of your Council

1:12:21.633 --> 1:12:24.094
and its history of deliberations.

1:12:24.094 --> 1:12:29.725
What you call "representative democracy"
is a most inefficient form of governance.

1:12:29.725 --> 1:12:31.393
- Maybe.

1:12:31.393 --> 1:12:34.104
But the one thing
you can say for democracy

1:12:34.104 --> 1:12:37.482
is that all other forms
of government are even worse.

1:12:38.442 --> 1:12:42.321
Over thousands of years
and on countless planets,

1:12:42.321 --> 1:12:44.865
it's the best system
anyone's ever come up with

1:12:44.865 --> 1:12:48.118
to ensure the strong
don't dominate the weak.

1:12:48.118 --> 1:12:50.162
At least not for long.

1:12:52.497 --> 1:12:55.792
[Kaylon speaking machine language]

1:13:00.756 --> 1:13:03.300
KAYLON PRIMARY:
We accept your terms.

1:13:05.511 --> 1:13:08.430
♪ tranquil music playing ♪

1:13:20.484 --> 1:13:26.323
MERCER: We are gathered here
in remembrance of a fallen shipmate.

1:13:28.283 --> 1:13:31.036
One who left us far too soon.

1:13:34.373 --> 1:13:37.626
Ensign Charly Burke will receive

1:13:37.626 --> 1:13:41.547
the Union Medal of Valor posthumously,

1:13:42.339 --> 1:13:45.050
for her unwavering sense of duty

1:13:47.302 --> 1:13:52.599
and for the ultimate sacrifice
in the pursuit of peace.

1:13:56.562 --> 1:13:57.729
No...

1:13:58.814 --> 1:14:00.274
medal...

1:14:01.149 --> 1:14:02.860
can bring her back.

1:14:04.778 --> 1:14:07.406
But we can acknowledge our debt

1:14:08.866 --> 1:14:11.201
to an outstanding Union officer

1:14:13.495 --> 1:14:16.582
and an extraordinary human being.

1:14:21.795 --> 1:14:23.714
Who would like to speak first?

1:14:26.466 --> 1:14:28.468
ISAAC: I wish to speak.

1:14:28.468 --> 1:14:30.387
♪

1:14:41.940 --> 1:14:46.278
Dr. Finn assisted me
with the construct of my statement.

1:14:46.278 --> 1:14:50.365
However, the substance is my own.

1:14:50.365 --> 1:14:52.826
I presume it will be adequate.

1:14:54.786 --> 1:14:58.123
Ensign Burke loved pancakes.

1:14:58.832 --> 1:15:02.127
She consumed them with butter
but no syrup

1:15:02.127 --> 1:15:07.132
and was indifferent to the addition
of berries or other condiments.

1:15:09.134 --> 1:15:13.388
As a child, pancakes
were her favorite breakfast.

1:15:15.807 --> 1:15:20.896
I served with Ensign Burke
for 257 days,

1:15:20.896 --> 1:15:25.108
17 minutes, and 49 seconds.

1:15:25.859 --> 1:15:31.823
And yet, my understanding
of her remained incomplete.

1:15:32.824 --> 1:15:35.744
She had an impressive brain
for a biological.

1:15:36.787 --> 1:15:40.958
She perceived the universe
in ways others could not.

1:15:42.668 --> 1:15:46.129
Ensign Burke
regarded me as an enemy.

1:15:47.756 --> 1:15:50.300
Yet despite her animosity,

1:15:50.884 --> 1:15:55.889
she chose to save my life
when no one else was able.

1:15:57.516 --> 1:16:00.435
And in the final seconds of her own life,

1:16:01.061 --> 1:16:06.692
Ensign Burke substantiated
for all the galaxy her true nature.

1:16:07.359 --> 1:16:11.864
One of integrity and selflessness.

1:16:13.574 --> 1:16:15.868
And in her sacrifice,

1:16:16.702 --> 1:16:22.165
she inspired the enemies of the Union
to become friends.

1:16:25.377 --> 1:16:27.629
Her existence was brief.

1:16:29.089 --> 1:16:33.802
But, much like the first domino
in a succession,

1:16:34.720 --> 1:16:39.141
her impact will be felt
far into the future.

1:16:46.899 --> 1:16:49.193
♪ contemplative music playing ♪

